# .gcloudignore passed via --ignore-file to ``gcloud builds submit``.
#
# gcloud tars the source directory (``/Users/ananth/Mobius``, the
# parent monorepo) and uploads it to Cloud Build. Without this file,
# every sibling repo + landing/ + .claude/ worktrees + node_modules
# ends up in the tarball — which is both 8+ GB and contains broken
# symlinks that crash gcloud mid-upload.
#
# Allow-list pattern mirrors the Dockerfile's .dockerignore. Only the
# four repos the Dockerfile COPYs should enter the build context.

*

# Un-exclude the repos chat actually needs.
!mobius-chat/
!mobius-contracts/
!mobius-skills-core/
!mobius-retriever/

# Prune noise within the four allowed repos.
**/.git/
**/.github/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/node_modules/
**/.DS_Store
**/.claude/

# Chat-specific exclusions (tests, docs, local artifacts).
mobius-chat/tests/
mobius-chat/docs/
mobius-chat/.venv/
mobius-chat/frontend/node_modules/
